main event: Two unidentified objects were observed by the crew of a KC-135 aircraft over the Atlantic on November 8, 1966, for approximately three hours.
interesting points: The objects were described as having visible lights, including one white flashing beacon and colored position lights., The objects maintained a trail formation with half-mile separation from the aircraft., The sighting occurred in darkness, which made the shape of the objects indiscernible., The FAA was contacted, and there were no scheduled flights in the vicinity at that time., The objects were visible for about one hour during the observation.
sighted object: two unidentified flying objects with flashing lights
witness description: crew members of a KC-135 aircraft including the aircraft commander, co-pilot, navigator, and boom operator
